metadata.name: The Huddling Shed in Winter
metadata.description:
I made this photograph during the catastrophic storm Arwen which left us without power for almost six days.

From my 15,000 Acres collection: A personal year-long study of a modern-day Scottish estate and the people who live and work there. 

This image will feature in the associated 15,000 Acres book which will be published in Summer 2022. The first buyer of this image will receive a signed copy of the book on publication. 

Near Miller's Bog, Glen Dye Estate
November 2021
Kodak Portra 400
3000 × 2250
